Key Match Events: Adam Zampa bowled Australia to a 33-run victory.
Chris Woakes (4-54) removed both the Australia openers.
Adil Rashid dismissed Smith and Josh Inglis in successive overs.
Jonny Bairstow fell for a first-ball duck.
Joe Root perished after a 17-ball stay.
Adam Zampa took 3 wickets for 21 runs, including the wickets of Buttler, Stokes, and Moeen.
England were dismissed for 253 in 48.1 overs.
Post-Match Reflections: Jos Buttler expressed concern over his own form and performance.
Buttler mentioned the team's disappointment and failure to meet expectations.
Speculation about the future of coach Matthew Mott.
